comments: [{'erwin_pteridophilos': "@edouardbruelhart @barbaraparris since i do know this species and it's wide variability the best, i do wonder about this individual, respectively individuals.\nSeveral leaves are clearly less deeply dissected than i expected at this site and upon their size, and they look quite rigid. Since that, these leaves look like representing a hybrid with either *P. lonchitis* = *P. × illyricum*, or perhaps, and less likely with *P. munitum* = *P. × arendsii*. It was worth to prove the spores' fertility to clear the possible hybrid status. Maybe there are different individuals, as some leaves got more dissected pinnae than others, causing me to agree with your ID. @murielbendel @fd_alsaker"}]
